NEW YORK POWER AUTHORITY WINS APPROVAL FOR NYC PLANTS
A New York environmental board has given approval to a state agency's plan to 
build 10 small power generators in New York City to help meet electricity 
demand this summer.
http://199.97.97.79/IMDS%PMADJN0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/djn/2001/
01/15/eng-djn/eng-djn_142026_2_78472225414589

MIDWEST ISO SUGGESTS NEW STRUCTURE TO MANAGE MIDWEST GRID
The Midwest Independent Transmission System Operator Inc. said Monday that it 
could form a new umbrella structure to help smooth the electric grid barriers 
that may arise if multiple grid management groups operate in the region.
http://199.97.97.79/IMDS%PMADJN0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/djn/2001/
01/15/eng-djn/eng-djn_190036_161_401815398131

SCOTTISHPOWER'S PACIFICORP FILES $142M UTAH RATE CASE
ScottishPower PLC (SPI) said Monday that its U.S. unit PacifiCorp filed a 
$142 million rate case request with the Utah Public Service Commission Jan. 
12.
